    faq2a: "A full energy audit (energy passport) costs between EUR 800 and EUR 2,500 depending on the size and complexity of the building. For a standard single-family house, expect around EUR 1,200 to EUR 1,500. The audit must be carried out by an energy consultant approved by the Ministry of Energy.",
    faq3q: "What is the impact of the energy class on property value?",
    faq3a: "According to the Observatoire de l'Habitat (2025), a class A property benefits from a premium of +5 to +8% compared to the reference class D. Conversely, a class G property suffers a discount of -12 to -16%, and a class I up to -25 to -30%. These gaps tend to widen as EPBD deadlines approach.",
